olive oil
1 apple
1 bag baby spinach leaves
3 clove garlic
1 packet penne
1 packet flaked almonds
1 packet diced bacon
20 g butter
½ bottle cream
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 packet basil pesto
1 tsp balsamic vinegar
1 bag salad leaves
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

Bring a medium saucepan of salted water to the boil. Thinly slice the apple (unpeeled). Roughly chop the baby spinach leaves. Finely chop the garlic.

Add the penne to the boiling water and cook until 'al dente', 10 minutes. Reserve some pasta water (1/4 cup for 2 people / 1/2 cup for 4 people), then drain and return the pasta to the saucepan. Drizzle with a little olive oil to prevent sticking and cover to keep warm.
TIP: 'Al dente' pasta is cooked through but still slightly firm in the centre.

While the pasta is cooking, heat a large frying pan over a medium-high heat. Add the flaked almonds and toast, tossing, until golden, 2-3 minutes. Transfer to a small bowl and set aside.

Return the frying pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Add the diced bacon and cook until golden, 4-5 minutes. Add the garlic and butter and cook until fragrant, 1-2 minutes. Add the longlife cream (see ingredients), chicken-style stock powder and reserved pasta water. Season with pepper and cook until slightly reduced, 2-3 minutes. Remove from the heat and stir through the baby spinach, basil pesto and cooked penne. Season to taste.

In a large bowl, combine the balsamic vinegar and a drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper. Add the mixed salad leaves and apple, then toss to combine.

Divide the creamy bacon and pesto penne between bowls and top with the grated Parmesan cheese. Serve with the apple salad and garnish with the toasted almonds.